node.text:
The Marieta Islands are a group of small uninhabited islands a few miles off the coast of Mexico. One of the popular tourist destination in the Islands is "love beach", also called the "hidden beach". It’s entirely hidden, and can only be reached by swimming through a short, narrow tunnel. While the beach itself is natural, the sinkhole is reportedly man-made. The Mexican government started using the islands as target practice prior to the First World War. These controlled bombings have formed numerous sinkholes. So, most likely a natural cave roof is collapsed due to bombings.
Video by @postandfly
